1
00:00:00,266 --> 00:00:03,381
That's the one. He came back
as a client for our company

2
00:00:03,406 --> 00:00:05,615
because of that
Pink Zipper campaign.

3
00:00:05,640 --> 00:00:06,840
Where your heart is,

4
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:09,022
that is your home.

5
00:00:09,047 --> 00:00:13,280
And I hope Singapore
will be a new home for you.

6
00:00:14,265 --> 00:00:15,625
Being 54...

7
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:18,800
It's not easy at all.

8
00:00:19,127 --> 00:00:20,975
They act like...

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,711
I'm not even living
in the same era as them.

10
00:00:23,736 --> 00:00:26,160
Please, help me find
a new door to open.

11
00:00:31,334 --> 00:00:32,600
"Tonight, I can sleep."

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,170
"Almost completely sound asleep."

13
00:00:36,084 --> 00:00:37,084
"But then..."

14
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:44,579
Jee, what's wrong?

15
00:00:44,604 --> 00:00:46,637
Sorry.

16
00:00:46,661 --> 00:00:49,121
Nothing. Go back to sleep.

17
00:00:50,721 --> 00:00:51,721
Okay.

18
00:01:50,895 --> 00:01:52,302
Stressed about tomorrow?

19
00:01:54,038 --> 00:01:55,038
No.

20
00:01:58,119 --> 00:01:59,910
Try to get some sleep.

21
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:02,200
So you'll look refreshing
when you wake up.

22
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,200
Hmm.

23
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,470
How should I dress tomorrow?

24
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:16,496
Asleep already?

25
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:21,360
Just dress nice.

26
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:34,403
Should we wake up early,
and stop for a haircut first?

27
00:02:38,924 --> 00:02:40,040
Yeah...

28
00:02:48,510 --> 00:02:49,914
Do we need to bring a gift?

29
00:02:49,939 --> 00:02:51,860
Hmm, good to have one.

30
00:02:51,885 --> 00:02:54,164
Thai sweets from
the shop by the alley?

31
00:02:54,189 --> 00:02:55,406
Hmm.

32
00:02:55,431 --> 00:02:58,821
Maybe flowers are better.
Eating too much sweets isn't good.

33
00:02:58,846 --> 00:03:00,175
Hmm.

34
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,775
All set then. Let's sleep.

35
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,000
How am I supposed to sleep, Jee?

36
00:03:16,697 --> 00:03:19,806
"Last night, I couldn't sleep."

37
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:21,875
"Too bad."

38
00:03:26,989 --> 00:03:27,989
Jee.

39
00:03:42,312 --> 00:03:43,312
Hmm...

40
00:04:07,988 --> 00:04:08,988
Shoot.

41
00:04:10,144 --> 00:04:11,516
Dark circles.

42
00:04:30,098 --> 00:04:32,360
Hey, which one's good?

43
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:34,773
Oh, Jee.

44
00:04:35,744 --> 00:04:37,255
You look good
whichever one you wear.

45
00:04:37,279 --> 00:04:38,360
Just put it on.

46
00:04:38,384 --> 00:04:42,255
Come on, help me choose.
If Mom and Dad aren't pleased,

47
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:44,800
and give us little inheritance.
Don't complain, then.

48
00:04:48,010 --> 00:04:49,010
This one.

49
00:04:49,698 --> 00:04:50,760
Okay.

50
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,240
Hey, Jee...

51
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,240
Hmm?

52
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:02,647
Do you really think
Mom and Dad will be okay?

53
00:05:06,092 --> 00:05:07,320
Of course they will.

54
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:12,440
Hurry up and go shower.

55
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:16,000
Quickly. We'll be late.

56
00:05:17,588 --> 00:05:19,360
Look at these dark circles!

57
00:05:19,385 --> 00:05:21,200
Hurry up or we'll be late!

58
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:36,680
- Bro.
- Hmm?

59
00:05:36,704 --> 00:05:39,273
Dressed up so nice
just to sign for a land transfer?

60
00:05:39,298 --> 00:05:40,378
Yeah.

61
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,600
- I have a meeting afterwards.
- Hmm.

62
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:45,880
- Gotta look nice.
- Um-hmm.

63
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,080
Here it is.

64
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:50,648
Look-Choup dessert
from that delicious shop.

65
00:05:50,673 --> 00:05:51,720
- Whoa.
- Ooh-hoo

66
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,440
I ordered extra today.
No need to fight over them.

67
00:05:54,465 --> 00:05:56,266
Oh, Mom...

68
00:05:56,291 --> 00:05:58,751
I'll pass for now.
I'm trying to lose weight.

69
00:05:58,776 --> 00:05:59,840
Good.

70
00:06:00,884 --> 00:06:04,657
Mom, do you really think
everyone likes your Look-Choup?

71
00:06:04,682 --> 00:06:07,448
I see only
your favorite son likes them.

72
00:06:07,473 --> 00:06:09,775
You steal mine all the time.

73
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:13,960
- Bro,
- Hmm?

74
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:16,840
Since you're so kind, you should
give this land to your nephew.

75
00:06:16,865 --> 00:06:19,423
- Take two more bites.
- No more.

76
00:06:19,448 --> 00:06:22,615
If you give the land
to that little monkey of his...

77
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:25,235
Don't forget Namtan,
my daughter too.

78
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:26,705
Alright, bro?

79
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:29,527
- Why give it to them?
- Probably many years away.

80
00:06:29,552 --> 00:06:32,283
Soon Jee will have kids.
He has to give it to his own kids.

81
00:06:32,308 --> 00:06:33,874
- Right.
- Yeah.

82
00:06:35,773 --> 00:06:37,493
Where should I
put this vase, Ma'am?

83
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:40,667
Uh...

84
00:06:41,582 --> 00:06:44,230
Uh... right here, Ohn. This way.

85
00:06:45,551 --> 00:06:47,200
Yeah, over there, son.

86
00:06:50,137 --> 00:06:52,135
Your friend is very polite.

87
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:55,280
There are many families
that teach their children well,

88
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,966
and still say Ma'am and Sir.

89
00:06:57,991 --> 00:06:59,520
Very nice.

90
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,600
Have a seat, son.

91
00:07:03,960 --> 00:07:07,841
Speaking of which, these days
people have kids easily, huh?

92
00:07:07,866 --> 00:07:09,920
What was it, Jang?
That thing...

93
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,960
They do the...
It starts with a G.

94
00:07:11,985 --> 00:07:14,040
- G...
- GIFT, Dad.

95
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,240
- Yeah, GIFT.
- GIFT.

96
00:07:15,264 --> 00:07:17,664
- Hmm.
- But Jee doesn't have a wife.

97
00:07:17,688 --> 00:07:19,655
He only has a close friend.

98
00:07:19,679 --> 00:07:22,365
Who would Jee take
to do GIFT with, Dad?

99
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:24,452
Yeah, and what's the other thing?

100
00:07:24,476 --> 00:07:26,411
The one where they have someone...

101
00:07:26,436 --> 00:07:28,409
- Get pregnant for them?
- Pregnant instead, yeah.

102
00:07:28,434 --> 00:07:29,662
It's called Surrogacy, Dad.

103
00:07:29,686 --> 00:07:31,427
- Yeah, Surrogacy.
- Surrogacy.

104
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:32,920
But for surrogacy, you need a wife.

105
00:07:32,944 --> 00:07:34,110
- Yeah, right.
- Oh really?

106
00:07:34,135 --> 00:07:36,296
Because they take the sperm and egg

107
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,775
from the husband and wife
and fertilize them outside.

108
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:42,688
Then inject it into the uterus
of the woman who is the surrogate.

109
00:07:42,713 --> 00:07:43,960
- I see.
- That's it.

110
00:07:44,463 --> 00:07:48,960
Dad, the flyer we got
from the hospital.

111
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,561
- Where is it?
- Oh right.

112
00:07:50,586 --> 00:07:52,027
Wait, where did I put it?

113
00:07:52,052 --> 00:07:53,452
- Let me go check.
- Go find it...

114
00:07:53,477 --> 00:07:55,607
- I'll show it to you.
- Wait a moment.

115
00:07:55,632 --> 00:07:57,062
Yeah, I'll bring it to you.

116
00:08:01,773 --> 00:08:02,773
Bro.

117
00:08:03,835 --> 00:08:06,720
Do you two really
want to have kids?

118
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:12,735
I don't think it would
be fair to the child.

119
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,166
The kid would be confused

120
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:17,413
because they won't have
correct gender role models.

121
00:08:18,885 --> 00:08:20,400
Correct gender role models?

122
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,976
How to put this...

123
00:08:24,696 --> 00:08:26,333
I'm not discriminating, bro.

124
00:08:26,358 --> 00:08:27,452
But think about it.

125
00:08:27,476 --> 00:08:30,820
A boy won't have
a father figure to imitate.

126
00:08:30,845 --> 00:08:33,240
And a girl won't have
a mother figure to imitate.

127
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:37,165
In the end,
they'll become troubled kids.

128
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,280
I haven't really thought
about having kids.

129
00:08:48,097 --> 00:08:51,376
But I don't see
how a child growing up in a family

130
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,600
with parents of the same gender
would have any problem.

131
00:08:56,502 --> 00:08:57,840
If that family...

132
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:01,383
can create a safe space
for the child to grow.

133
00:09:02,713 --> 00:09:05,643
There are plenty
of straight couples,

134
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,840
who raise their kids terribly.

135
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:13,267
Don't use gender to judge
what makes a good parent.

136
00:09:13,292 --> 00:09:14,292
Please.

137
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,440
Come on, you're younger
than him for nothing.

138
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:24,567
Your thinking is
so old and ancient.

139
00:09:24,592 --> 00:09:26,695
Look how far
the world has moved on.

140
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,280
I agree with Ohn.

141
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,640
No matter what gender
the parents are,

142
00:09:30,640 --> 00:09:34,135
everyone has the rights
to raise a child just the same.

143
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,783
But the most important thing is

144
00:09:35,807 --> 00:09:38,250
you should have a child
when you are ready.

145
00:09:38,275 --> 00:09:39,295
Hmm.

146
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:42,120
Alright. I apologize then.

147
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:45,440
I do agree with
having a child when ready.

148
00:09:46,400 --> 00:09:49,753
But as for you two,
I think you aren't ready anymore.

149
00:09:49,778 --> 00:09:50,891
Think about it...

150
00:09:50,915 --> 00:09:55,127
Having a kid when you're old,
you can't run after them.

151
00:09:55,152 --> 00:09:57,125
You're better off raising
your niece and nephew.

152
00:09:57,149 --> 00:09:58,538
Think about it.

153
00:09:58,562 --> 00:10:01,200
I have a kid as your nephew.
You raise him. Okay?

154
00:10:02,520 --> 00:10:04,720
Here, got it for you, Jee.

155
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Here you go, son.

156
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:15,335
"Sperm Bank"
If you haven't found the one,

157
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:18,055
you can deposit your sperm.

158
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:22,136
That way, if you meet
your soulmate when you're older,

159
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,240
you can still have children.

160
00:10:27,393 --> 00:10:28,689
Do I need to sign anything else?

161
00:10:28,713 --> 00:10:30,536
This is all signed.

162
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,440
If it's all signed,
then nothing else.

163
00:10:32,440 --> 00:10:33,680
Okay, then...

164
00:10:34,597 --> 00:10:36,135
- I'm heading back.
- Huh?

165
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,201
Going already?

166
00:10:37,231 --> 00:10:39,000
- Bye.
- Okay, bye.

167
00:10:39,025 --> 00:10:40,427
- Bye, Mom.
- Bye bye.

168
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,400
- Okay.
- Bye, Jee.

169
00:10:43,799 --> 00:10:44,799
Let's go.

170
00:10:46,576 --> 00:10:47,576
Come on.

171
00:10:49,287 --> 00:10:51,120
- Why did you say that?
- I didn't mean to.

172
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,000
I just said what I was thinking.

173
00:11:09,792 --> 00:11:10,800
Jee...

174
00:11:11,280 --> 00:11:12,760
Jee, wait a second, son.

175
00:11:13,706 --> 00:11:14,706
Here.

176
00:11:15,859 --> 00:11:17,560
Take some snacks with you.

177
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:18,960
Oh...

178
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,899
Mom...

179
00:11:22,924 --> 00:11:24,946
I don't want to have kids.

180
00:11:24,971 --> 00:11:28,856
Just take it in case you
change your mind later.

181
00:11:29,417 --> 00:11:31,160
Leaving already?

182
00:11:32,198 --> 00:11:34,520
Yes. Okay, I'm off.

183
00:11:34,545 --> 00:11:35,640
- Sawasdee krub.
- Yes, yes.

184
00:11:35,664 --> 00:11:36,664
Bye.

185
00:11:38,771 --> 00:11:39,824
Good luck, son.

186
00:11:40,677 --> 00:11:42,613
And that person who came with Jira,

187
00:11:42,638 --> 00:11:43,973
that's not his younger brother.

188
00:11:43,998 --> 00:11:46,215
No, that's his friend.

189
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:48,240
A colleague.
They do business together.

190
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,800
At this age
and still no girlfriend?

191
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,917
Oh well. Men, right?

192
00:11:53,941 --> 00:11:56,803
He still has plenty of time
to find the right one.

193
00:12:13,517 --> 00:12:15,203
You're uncomfortable too, huh?

194
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:21,263
Well, you looked so stressed
ever since we left the house.

195
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:27,760
Sorry. Every time we go
to my house, it's just stressful.

196
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,800
My house really
isn't a safe space, is it?

197
00:12:33,915 --> 00:12:35,561
It's okay.

198
00:12:36,121 --> 00:12:38,141
We got through it, didn't we?

199
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,913
Right...

200
00:12:40,937 --> 00:12:42,937
you have a meeting
with a client, right?

201
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:45,360
You can drop me off over there.

202
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,680
I'll take a taxi
the rest of the way.

203
00:12:48,542 --> 00:12:49,542
Where are you going?

204
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:51,387
Well, to visit my mom, I guess.

205
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:55,120
Seeing you with your family
made me miss my mom.

206
00:12:56,170 --> 00:12:57,843
Good, I'll go with you, then.

207
00:12:58,604 --> 00:13:00,720
Huh? What about your client?

208
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,417
There is no client.

209
00:13:05,740 --> 00:13:06,740
Mister!

210
00:13:09,591 --> 00:13:10,896
"Nice try"

211
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:35,346
Feel free to look around...

212
00:13:35,371 --> 00:13:37,251
Oh, Ohn!

213
00:13:37,276 --> 00:13:38,488
Hello, Mom.

214
00:13:38,513 --> 00:13:40,615
Why didn't you tell me
you were coming?

215
00:13:40,640 --> 00:13:43,480
I missed you.
Come here, come here.

216
00:13:47,927 --> 00:13:49,248
Let's go inside.

217
00:13:49,273 --> 00:13:51,760
This way. Come on.

218
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:59,166
Oh, I wondered who it was.
It's the Beloved Son himself.

219
00:13:59,191 --> 00:14:01,295
Someone's jealous.

220
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:03,040
Watch your mouth.

221
00:14:03,065 --> 00:14:04,960
If I knew you'd be this sassy,

222
00:14:04,985 --> 00:14:06,855
I would've smothered you
when Mom was busy.

223
00:14:06,856 --> 00:14:08,701
What? Mom...

224
00:14:08,726 --> 00:14:10,655
Aom is being mean to me. Help!

225
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:13,548
Aom, stop teasing your brother.

226
00:14:13,573 --> 00:14:15,760
You're always teasing your brother.

227
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:17,680
Hello, Aom.

228
00:14:17,705 --> 00:14:21,329
Hello, Jira.
Still handsome as ever.

229
00:14:21,354 --> 00:14:23,658
When are you going to dump Ohn?

230
00:14:23,683 --> 00:14:26,036
- Hey!
- He is a bad influence, you know.

231
00:14:26,630 --> 00:14:28,447
- You evil woman!
- Seriously!

232
00:14:28,472 --> 00:14:29,659
Mom, look...

233
00:14:29,683 --> 00:14:32,815
Aom wants Jee to dump me
so I'll be a divorcee like her!

234
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:36,711
I have such weird children.
They're arguing all the time.

235
00:14:36,736 --> 00:14:38,215
But Jira,

236
00:14:38,239 --> 00:14:40,775
if Ohn's a little weird sometimes,
please don't leave him, okay?

237
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,185
- Mom!
- Oh...

238
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,775
- Uncle Ohn.
- Ikkyu.

239
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,640
I missed you so much.

240
00:14:50,378 --> 00:14:51,680
I missed you too!

241
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,735
Can you help me figure out
the dance moves for Nokko's song!

242
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:57,168
Huh? Nokko released a new song?

243
00:14:57,193 --> 00:14:59,520
Uncle Ohn, you really are old!

244
00:14:59,544 --> 00:15:01,273
You've never heard
Nokko's new song?

245
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,440
Ikkyu.

246
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,726
Say hi to Uncle Jee first.

247
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:08,415
Before you start gossiping,
mind your manners.

248
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:09,600
- Right.
- Mmm.

249
00:15:10,971 --> 00:15:12,184
- Sawasdee ka.
- Yes, hello.

250
00:15:13,245 --> 00:15:14,825
So polite like me, isn't he?

251
00:15:16,337 --> 00:15:18,048
I'm borrowing him for a sec, okay?

252
00:15:18,073 --> 00:15:19,073
Sure.

253
00:15:19,098 --> 00:15:20,098
Let's go, Uncle Ohn.

254
00:15:20,753 --> 00:15:21,753
- Be right back.
- Mmm.

255
00:15:23,807 --> 00:15:26,563
They love each other so much.

256
00:15:26,588 --> 00:15:28,884
They always have
something to talk about.

257
00:15:28,909 --> 00:15:29,909
Come on.

258
00:15:31,909 --> 00:15:33,120
Let me see.

259
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:35,080
How's the new song?

260
00:15:35,080 --> 00:15:37,440
Turn it on. Let's watch.

261
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,344
You dance along with me, okay?

262
00:15:39,369 --> 00:15:40,388
Alright, okay.

263
00:15:41,980 --> 00:15:44,320
Do we have to record it too?

264
00:15:44,881 --> 00:15:45,960
Just for watching later.

265
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,520
Okay, come on.

266
00:15:47,545 --> 00:15:48,585
Ready?

267
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:49,960
Ready.

268
00:16:03,543 --> 00:16:04,543
Ouch...

269
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:05,840
Ooh-ho.

270
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:08,718
I think I did that move wrong.

271
00:16:08,742 --> 00:16:10,488
- My knee hurts.
- Oh, Uncle Ohn...

272
00:16:10,513 --> 00:16:11,640
Don't slack off!

273
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:16,071
If you don't practice hard,
the path to the stars...

274
00:16:16,096 --> 00:16:18,436
will get narrower and narrower.

275
00:16:18,461 --> 00:16:19,562
Nokko said so.

276
00:16:19,888 --> 00:16:23,801
Then let Nokko dance by herself.

277
00:16:23,826 --> 00:16:25,975
I'm not going to the star with her.

278
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,846
I can't do this. My knee hurts.

279
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,640
Uncle Ohn, don't act so old.

280
00:16:34,157 --> 00:16:35,360
I'll give you a massage.

281
00:16:37,962 --> 00:16:40,521
Stay with me for a long time, okay?

282
00:16:40,546 --> 00:16:41,753
I'm still just a kid.

283
00:16:41,777 --> 00:16:45,032
I can't support two oldies
and a grandma yet.

284
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:49,080
Easy there, Ikkyu.

285
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,240
I wasn't planning to rely on you.

286
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:56,971
I just want you to grow up
and be able to support yourself.

287
00:16:56,995 --> 00:16:58,627
Don't be a burden to anyone else.

288
00:16:58,651 --> 00:17:00,297
That's enough to make me happy.

289
00:17:01,706 --> 00:17:04,761
But Mom told me
to take care of you too.

290
00:17:04,786 --> 00:17:06,458
She said that because you're gay,

291
00:17:06,482 --> 00:17:09,052
when you get old,
you might have no one.

292
00:17:21,131 --> 00:17:22,400
Mmm-hmm.

293
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:25,904
- Not too much, Mom.
- Hmm?

294
00:17:25,929 --> 00:17:27,289
It's not very healthy.

295
00:17:27,496 --> 00:17:30,360
Oh, please. At my age...

296
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:33,507
Healthy or not,
don't worry too much.

297
00:17:35,826 --> 00:17:36,900
- Delicious.
- Yummy.

298
00:17:36,925 --> 00:17:38,245
Sweet.

299
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:42,415
How about you two?
Still loving each other?

300
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:45,394
Oh Mom, you ask me that
every time you see me.

301
00:17:45,419 --> 00:17:48,316
We haven't had
any fights lately at all.

302
00:17:48,341 --> 00:17:49,840
Really? Good.

303
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,003
But let me warn you...

304
00:17:52,027 --> 00:17:54,655
If you stay loving like this
for a long time, I'm happy.

305
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:56,784
But if you ever do fight...

306
00:17:56,809 --> 00:17:59,946
Absolutely forbidden, I beg you,
don't slap or hit each other.

307
00:17:59,946 --> 00:18:00,946
Oh!

308
00:18:00,971 --> 00:18:02,960
Breaking up already
leaves scars on the heart.

309
00:18:02,984 --> 00:18:05,677
If you start hitting each other,
you'll have scars on the body too.

310
00:18:06,730 --> 00:18:10,034
We've been together this long.
Don't you trust me yet, Mom?

311
00:18:10,059 --> 00:18:12,220
I do trust you.
Just saying it, that's all.

312
00:18:12,245 --> 00:18:13,760
Mmm.

313
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:17,216
What about you?
Is the shop still doing okay?

314
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:19,719
It sells enough to get by.

315
00:18:19,744 --> 00:18:22,547
Since that 24-hour store opened,

316
00:18:22,572 --> 00:18:25,320
it took all my cash customers away.

317
00:18:25,345 --> 00:18:26,705
The ones who buy from me?

318
00:18:26,730 --> 00:18:28,400
- All on credit.
- Oh!

319
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,320
Anyone with cash flocks over there.

320
00:18:31,544 --> 00:18:33,558
Oh...right.

321
00:18:33,922 --> 00:18:34,962
What's this now?

322
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:37,487
Here, take this.

323
00:18:38,498 --> 00:18:40,120
Just take it.

324
00:18:41,731 --> 00:18:43,254
No, don't want it.

325
00:18:43,286 --> 00:18:46,292
So you have some cash to use
while you wait for them to pay.

326
00:18:46,317 --> 00:18:48,141
If I'm short on anything,

327
00:18:48,165 --> 00:18:50,775
Aom covers it anyway. It's fine.

328
00:18:50,800 --> 00:18:51,923
No, no.

329
00:18:51,947 --> 00:18:55,120
This is Ohn asked me
to give it to you.

330
00:18:55,145 --> 00:18:56,753
- He forgot to get some cash.
- Oh.

331
00:18:56,778 --> 00:18:59,840
I just remembered right now.
It's not my money, it's Ohn's.

332
00:18:59,865 --> 00:19:01,160
It's Ohn's money for sure?

333
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,320
- Sure.
- Ah...

334
00:19:02,556 --> 00:19:04,469
Thank you, dear.
I'll keep it, then.

335
00:19:05,654 --> 00:19:07,760
Food's ready. Let's eat!

336
00:19:08,088 --> 00:19:10,360
Let's go eat.

337
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,720
I'm closing the shop
to eat with my babies!

338
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:14,205
Ooh-ho!

339
00:19:14,330 --> 00:19:15,720
- We go all out.
- Come on.

340
00:19:15,907 --> 00:19:17,520
Have a seat.

341
00:19:22,211 --> 00:19:23,211
- Jee.
- Huh?

342
00:19:24,499 --> 00:19:25,499
What?

343
00:19:25,937 --> 00:19:26,937
Thank you.

344
00:19:28,760 --> 00:19:29,760
For what?

345
00:19:30,935 --> 00:19:33,440
Well, for giving money to Mom.

346
00:19:34,066 --> 00:19:35,072
Mmm...

347
00:19:36,186 --> 00:19:39,040
She said sales
haven't been good lately.

348
00:19:39,064 --> 00:19:41,172
There's a competition.

349
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:47,920
We keep the shop open
just so she isn't lonely.

350
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:51,160
Don't worry about the income.

351
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:56,120
I was thinking, when I retire...

352
00:19:56,800 --> 00:19:59,840
I planned to come back and
take over the shop from Mom.

353
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:00,920
Mmm.

354
00:20:00,945 --> 00:20:03,064
But with sales like this...

355
00:20:03,089 --> 00:20:04,880
What am I going to do when I'm old?

356
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,480
Right here.

357
00:20:09,626 --> 00:20:10,826
I'll take care of you.

358
00:20:13,383 --> 00:20:17,455
Listen, I save money every month...

359
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:20,760
If we spend it carefully,
it's enough to last a lifetime.

360
00:20:41,105 --> 00:20:42,240
What is it, Jee?

361
00:20:43,982 --> 00:20:45,080
Let me see.

362
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:53,142
"Dad really wants you
to go freeze your sperms."

363
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:55,280
"If you have time,
go do it for him."

364
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,880
"As for the land,
give it to my kid."

365
00:20:58,066 --> 00:21:00,366
"I'll make sure he takes care
of you well until you die."

366
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:03,147
"P.S. Jang reminded me
that next week..."

367
00:21:03,172 --> 00:21:05,663
"don't forget Mom's 72nd Birthday."

368
00:21:05,688 --> 00:21:07,383
- Mmm.
- "Don't miss it."

369
00:21:07,798 --> 00:21:08,798
Mmm.

370
00:21:23,815 --> 00:21:24,815
Ohn.

371
00:21:25,891 --> 00:21:26,891
Ohn.

372
00:21:27,473 --> 00:21:28,473
Hey!

373
00:21:30,241 --> 00:21:31,880
Get up now!

374
00:21:31,905 --> 00:21:34,293
What is it now, Jee?

375
00:21:34,318 --> 00:21:35,905
Let's go to the gym.

376
00:21:35,930 --> 00:21:37,175
Right now?

377
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,480
Come on, your sister
made so much food.

378
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:42,472
- I feel fat already. Come on!
- No way...

379
00:21:42,497 --> 00:21:45,105
Don't be lazy. Don't let me
hear you complain about being fat.

380
00:21:45,130 --> 00:21:48,583
I'm not lazy. I was just
lying down thinking about work.

381
00:21:49,828 --> 00:21:50,927
Seriously!

382
00:21:50,951 --> 00:21:54,045
I'm trying to figure out
how to help Mom's shop.

383
00:21:54,070 --> 00:21:57,640
Excuses, excuses!

384
00:21:59,231 --> 00:22:00,244
Jee!

385
00:22:01,665 --> 00:22:02,869
Jee.

386
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,243
You'll see...

387
00:22:07,665 --> 00:22:11,183
how my soft power
help my mom's shop!

388
00:22:14,386 --> 00:22:15,613
Whatever floats your boat.

389
00:22:17,530 --> 00:22:18,530
Jee.

390
00:22:19,015 --> 00:22:20,058
Jee!

391
00:22:20,083 --> 00:22:21,280
Wait...wait, Jee!

392
00:22:21,305 --> 00:22:24,343
Put my leg down. Cramp...Jee!

393
00:22:25,024 --> 00:22:26,440
Oww!

394
00:22:27,432 --> 00:22:30,440
Oww...Jee!

395
00:22:32,571 --> 00:22:34,280
My sweet nap.

396
00:23:40,448 --> 00:23:41,556
"Sweets, this way."

397
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,800
How was that? Fun, huh?

398
00:23:55,608 --> 00:23:57,720
Do you really want me
to do the Nha Harn dance?

399
00:23:59,892 --> 00:24:01,186
No.

400
00:24:01,211 --> 00:24:03,591
I just wanted to show you that

401
00:24:03,616 --> 00:24:06,615
you should dance
however you want to dance.

402
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:10,320
Because dancing is about
expressing ourselves freely.

403
00:24:10,691 --> 00:24:12,495
Enjoy the music.

404
00:24:12,520 --> 00:24:15,040
Dance like nobody is watching.

405
00:24:16,283 --> 00:24:17,291
Mmm.

406
00:24:17,316 --> 00:24:19,360
Basically, what I'm saying is...

407
00:24:20,411 --> 00:24:23,707
If you're thinking too much,
you won't enjoy dancing, sweetie.

408
00:24:23,732 --> 00:24:24,851
Just dance!

409
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,227
But I want to dance
Nokko's moves perfectly.

410
00:24:29,972 --> 00:24:35,216
Oh boy. Nokko's song is fast
and the moves are quite hard.

411
00:24:35,993 --> 00:24:37,376
Quite difficult.

412
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:40,975
Why don't you ask your friends
to help you figure out the moves?

413
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:42,610
I couldn't even follow the clip.

414
00:24:43,477 --> 00:24:45,136
I'm scared they will bully me.

415
00:24:53,903 --> 00:24:55,082
Remember this, Ikkyu.

416
00:24:56,645 --> 00:24:59,800
If anyone bullies you,
just punch them.

417
00:25:03,325 --> 00:25:05,280
Wait, no. That's not good.
Don't do that.

418
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,155
Better not punch them.

419
00:25:07,180 --> 00:25:10,720
We shouldn't use violence
to solve problems.

420
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:14,520
Let's just say,
cursing them out is enough.

421
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:17,916
Like... "You outdated people!"

422
00:25:17,941 --> 00:25:19,775
"Dinosaurs!"

423
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:21,775
"Zero creativity!"

424
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:24,920
"Always picking on
people's bodies and gender!"

425
00:25:24,945 --> 00:25:26,764
"If you want to live in
the dark ages so badly..."

426
00:25:26,789 --> 00:25:28,776
"...go build a time machine
if you're smart enough!"

427
00:25:28,801 --> 00:25:31,463
"Go back in time
like Michael J. Fox!"

428
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:34,160
And after you curse them out,
dance Nokko's moves in their face.

429
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:37,669
But if you can't remember the moves

430
00:25:37,694 --> 00:25:39,120
just do the Nha Harn dance.

431
00:25:39,120 --> 00:25:40,578
Go wild!

432
00:25:40,602 --> 00:25:44,255
Stun them so much that
they forget to bully you.

433
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,400
That sounds better, right?

434
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:48,827
Come on...

435
00:25:48,851 --> 00:25:50,657
Let's practice the Nha Harn dance.

436
00:25:50,681 --> 00:25:52,230
I'll play the music.

437
00:25:54,539 --> 00:25:55,790
Ahh...

438
00:26:10,914 --> 00:26:12,574
"Fresh eggs"
"This shelf's on sale."

439
00:26:14,171 --> 00:26:15,567
"Look around"

440
00:26:28,297 --> 00:26:29,360
Peek-a-boo!

441
00:26:29,695 --> 00:26:31,320
Jee!

442
00:26:32,584 --> 00:26:33,720
You scared me!

443
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:37,000
Sorry, I didn't think
you'd be that scared.

444
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:41,507
You snuck up on me like a ghost.
Anyone would be scared.

445
00:26:41,532 --> 00:26:44,512
Well, I saw you
smiling all to yourself.

446
00:26:44,537 --> 00:26:46,968
What were you doing?
Looking at naked guys?

447
00:26:46,993 --> 00:26:49,360
Here, come take a look.

448
00:26:51,454 --> 00:26:52,454
Ooh!

449
00:26:52,975 --> 00:26:53,975
Wow.

450
00:26:55,077 --> 00:26:56,077
Cute.

451
00:26:57,202 --> 00:27:00,200
Well, the artist has skills.

452
00:27:00,536 --> 00:27:03,671
Mmm... I think

453
00:27:03,696 --> 00:27:06,829
You could turn them into stickers
and sell them online!

454
00:27:06,854 --> 00:27:08,335
- Really?
- Mmm.

455
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:09,769
You really think they'd sell?

456
00:27:15,446 --> 00:27:16,446
Jee.

457
00:27:17,829 --> 00:27:19,560
Don't be jealous of yourself...

458
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:23,695
for having a boyfriend who is
both talented and handsome.

459
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:25,240
Mmm...

460
00:27:25,815 --> 00:27:28,642
Actually, what's more enviable

461
00:27:28,666 --> 00:27:31,086
is having a family
that understands you.

462
00:27:33,158 --> 00:27:34,200
Jee...

463
00:27:35,726 --> 00:27:37,726
Sometimes my mom
doesn't understand me either.

464
00:27:38,566 --> 00:27:40,313
She sometimes asks me

465
00:27:40,337 --> 00:27:42,600
when I'm going to
ordain as a monk for her.

466
00:27:42,625 --> 00:27:45,000
Well, why don't you?

467
00:27:45,601 --> 00:27:47,450
Are you afraid of missing dinner?

468
00:27:47,928 --> 00:27:49,408
Is that it?

469
00:27:49,433 --> 00:27:51,624
Yeah, I'm chubby.

470
00:27:52,855 --> 00:27:55,338
I might be chubby,
but I'm delicious.

471
00:27:55,363 --> 00:27:56,400
Oh...

472
00:27:57,040 --> 00:28:00,015
Are you sure you won't get jealous?

473
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:03,375
If I go live in a temple
surrounded by men?

474
00:28:03,400 --> 00:28:04,560
Mmm...

475
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:08,692
I guess I couldn't help it.
I'd have to move on,

476
00:28:08,717 --> 00:28:11,840
and give my heart to Room 405.

477
00:28:13,135 --> 00:28:14,306
Who?

478
00:28:14,331 --> 00:28:16,040
Room 405.

479
00:28:17,112 --> 00:28:18,240
What's his name?

480
00:28:18,265 --> 00:28:19,883
Why do you want to know?

481
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:21,680
Where did you meet him?

482
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:24,200
At the pool or the gym?

483
00:28:24,225 --> 00:28:26,536
Wherever people
with good bodies meet?

484
00:28:26,561 --> 00:28:29,760
Good body too?
Like... zero body fat good?

485
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,840
I didn't look at his body.
I only looked at his face.

486
00:28:33,315 --> 00:28:34,976
Does anyone have anything else?

487
00:28:36,284 --> 00:28:37,317
Nothing.

488
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:41,190
If there's nothing else,
let's get to work.

489
00:28:41,215 --> 00:28:42,900
Meeting adjourned.

490
00:28:42,925 --> 00:28:43,968
Thank you.

491
00:29:03,219 --> 00:29:04,497
What's up, Jang?

492
00:29:04,522 --> 00:29:06,487
You can make it
to Mom's birthday, right?

493
00:29:06,512 --> 00:29:07,512
Yeah. I'm going.

494
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:09,047
Here's the thing,

495
00:29:09,072 --> 00:29:12,615
Mom wants to invite her
old friends to join the party.

496
00:29:12,640 --> 00:29:15,240
So it's going to be
bigger than I thought.

497
00:29:15,969 --> 00:29:18,585
Mmm. Need any help?

498
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:21,360
No need. But...

499
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:24,008
Can you not bring Ohn?

500
00:29:24,033 --> 00:29:26,483
I'm afraid Mom will be embarrassed
in front of her friends.

501
00:29:34,495 --> 00:29:35,796
Ohn is joining to the party.

502
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:00,880
Jee...

503
00:30:03,160 --> 00:30:06,050
Lilly, my friend's daughter,
is cute, isn't she?

504
00:30:06,075 --> 00:30:08,390
Can't you help tutor her a bit?

505
00:30:08,920 --> 00:30:11,216
She'll be your junior
at the university soon.

506
00:30:11,792 --> 00:30:14,200
No, Mom. It's a waste
of my study time.

507
00:30:16,275 --> 00:30:17,275
Jee...

508
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:19,760
Son.

509
00:30:20,240 --> 00:30:21,240
Jee...

510
00:30:21,520 --> 00:30:22,520
Jee...

511
00:30:23,169 --> 00:30:24,200
Son.

512
00:30:24,224 --> 00:30:25,224
Jee...

513
00:30:25,435 --> 00:30:28,535
Jenny sent flowers
to congratulate you.

514
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:29,753
Take them, son.

515
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,880
Take a picture with it
and send it to her.

516
00:30:35,228 --> 00:30:37,815
Mom, I'm allergic to pollens.

517
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:39,040
It just started.

518
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,534
- Jee...
- Hmm?

519
00:30:42,345 --> 00:30:44,960
This weekend, take Oy
to make merit, won't you?

520
00:30:47,889 --> 00:30:50,312
I can't. I have a company outing.

521
00:30:57,175 --> 00:30:58,300
My dear,

522
00:30:59,078 --> 00:31:01,078
when are you going
to have a girlfriend, son?

523
00:31:02,157 --> 00:31:07,335
Jenny, Lilly, and Oy,
the ones I introduced you to,

524
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:09,400
they all have
two or three kids by now.

525
00:31:14,741 --> 00:31:17,280
You still haven't found
a girl you like, have you?

526
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,800
- Jira.
- Hmm?

527
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:32,032
The executive meeting about
the new brand starts in 5 minutes.

528
00:31:32,057 --> 00:31:33,057
Oh.

529
00:31:33,081 --> 00:31:34,094
Okay.

530
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:44,320
Yeah, thank you.

531
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:47,200
I'll try not to worry too much.

532
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:51,135
If he's really flirting
with that kid in Room 405,

533
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,623
he wouldn't have told me, right?

534
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:54,855
Oh, Ohn.

535
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:57,480
Do you ever learn
to trust your boyfriend?

536
00:31:58,280 --> 00:32:00,478
If Jee really wanted
to break up with you,

537
00:32:00,503 --> 00:32:02,799
he wouldn't have
waited for the 7th year.

538
00:32:02,823 --> 00:32:05,122
He would have dumped you ages ago.

539
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:08,481
And if he really does
break up with you, don't worry.

540
00:32:08,506 --> 00:32:10,356
Once I get to Canada,

541
00:32:10,380 --> 00:32:13,239
I'll be an agent and find
a Farang boyfriend for you myself.

542
00:32:13,926 --> 00:32:17,215
But you really need to
adjust your attitude also.

543
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:19,335
Fine, enough already.

544
00:32:19,360 --> 00:32:22,015
No need to preach me
about relationships.

545
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:24,255
End of story.
Don't drag it out.

546
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:27,653
That's it. See you Saturday
at Mae Champi's house. Bye.

547
00:32:27,678 --> 00:32:28,920
Yeah. Bye.

548
00:32:38,512 --> 00:32:39,560
Hello?

549
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:41,760
The stickers you ordered are ready.

550
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,403
Okay. I'll go pick them up.

551
00:32:45,428 --> 00:32:46,428
Okay.

552
00:32:59,829 --> 00:33:02,160
Going down.

553
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:06,720
Uh... actually.

554
00:33:07,243 --> 00:33:08,640
I'll ride down with you.

555
00:33:21,699 --> 00:33:24,469
"I guess I couldn't help it.
I'd have to move on,"

556
00:33:24,494 --> 00:33:27,320
"and give my heart to Room 405."

557
00:33:27,838 --> 00:33:28,838
405.

558
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:30,640
405.

559
00:33:36,160 --> 00:33:40,040
Son, will the stickers
really make sales better?

560
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,735
Better or not, I don't know, Mom.

561
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:46,800
But customers can just walk in
and pick things themselves now.

562
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:51,160
You won't have to hobble around
grabbing stuff for them anymore.

563
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:55,540
It's just a little bit of
exercise for me, you know.

564
00:33:57,280 --> 00:33:58,920
You don't like what I did for you?

565
00:33:58,920 --> 00:34:02,920
I like it. Whatever my child
does for me, I like it all.

566
00:34:04,129 --> 00:34:06,064
If it doesn't sell well,

567
00:34:06,088 --> 00:34:08,982
maybe you should just
stop selling altogether.

568
00:34:09,520 --> 00:34:12,720
Just stay home and relax.
Aom and I can take care of you.

569
00:34:14,564 --> 00:34:17,200
You know what
'selling for society' means?

570
00:34:17,541 --> 00:34:20,756
I sell a little, make some money
here and there. I save it up.

571
00:34:21,131 --> 00:34:23,960
I'm not being
a burden to anyone at all.

572
00:34:24,394 --> 00:34:26,160
Just selling for fun, you know?

573
00:34:26,707 --> 00:34:29,347
Okay. Whatever makes you happy.

574
00:34:29,589 --> 00:34:32,880
And this cartoon thing,
was it expensive?

575
00:34:33,735 --> 00:34:34,761
Oh Mom!

576
00:34:35,345 --> 00:34:37,829
I can afford it.

577
00:34:38,319 --> 00:34:40,520
I know you can afford it.

578
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:42,920
But you don't have to
spend so much on me.

579
00:34:42,945 --> 00:34:46,120
Save it for yourself
for when you get old.

580
00:34:46,947 --> 00:34:49,440
I still have Jee, Mom.

581
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:51,800
We have each other.

582
00:34:52,625 --> 00:34:53,920
Don't worry about me.

583
00:34:55,160 --> 00:34:56,720
And what if Jee leaves you?

584
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:59,640
How will you
take care of yourself then?

585
00:35:03,302 --> 00:35:05,960
I still have some savings.

586
00:35:08,080 --> 00:35:10,921
I understand that you
can take care of yourself.

587
00:35:10,946 --> 00:35:14,015
But Ikkyu, he's just like you.

588
00:35:14,040 --> 00:35:16,080
Whatever happens,
you still have your sister.

589
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:18,920
You have Aom. If anything happens,
siblings can help each other.

590
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,920
But Ikkyu is an only child.

591
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,120
Oh, Mom.

592
00:35:22,796 --> 00:35:26,255
By the time Ikkyu grows up,
our country will be developed.

593
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:28,815
We'll have universal welfare.

594
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:32,860
No matter what gender,
everyone will be treated equally.

595
00:35:32,885 --> 00:35:35,455
No wife, no kids, no husband...

596
00:35:35,455 --> 00:35:38,240
From birth to death,
the government takes care of you.

597
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,945
You don't have to worry about him.

598
00:35:41,406 --> 00:35:43,384
If it can really be like that,
that would be good.

599
00:35:43,408 --> 00:35:45,256
I could die in peace.

600
00:35:47,138 --> 00:35:48,138
Go on, dear.

601
00:35:51,823 --> 00:35:55,320
"Thank you for supporting us!"

602
00:36:07,150 --> 00:36:08,584
Did you go to the publisher today?

603
00:36:08,608 --> 00:36:10,163
I didn't know.

604
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:12,760
I went to Mom's house, Jee.

605
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:17,187
I went to put up those stickers.

606
00:36:17,212 --> 00:36:20,655
- Ah, Mom's house.
- Mmm.

607
00:36:20,655 --> 00:36:23,960
Hey, this Saturday,
go to my house again, okay?

608
00:36:24,686 --> 00:36:25,686
It's Mom's birthday.

609
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:28,400
- This Saturday?
- Mmm.

610
00:36:28,943 --> 00:36:29,943
I can't.

611
00:36:30,920 --> 00:36:31,920
Why not?

612
00:36:32,183 --> 00:36:36,775
I made plans with Chon and Thai
to go visit Mae Champi.

613
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,336
We planned a whole day for her.

614
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:43,200
Just do it another day.
This Saturday go to my Mom's.

615
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:48,836
Does your mom really want me to go?

616
00:36:49,539 --> 00:36:50,632
Yes.

617
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:56,520
I can't change the program.

618
00:36:57,121 --> 00:37:00,448
Mae Champi's favorite Morlam band
is playing this Saturday too.

619
00:37:00,473 --> 00:37:02,975
I want to take her out
and be outside for awhile.

620
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:06,096
Before she gets
depressed and bedridden.

621
00:37:23,942 --> 00:37:27,613
Or maybe invite your mom
to dance Nha Harn with us?

622
00:37:27,638 --> 00:37:30,640
Come on. Don't joke around.

623
00:37:30,640 --> 00:37:32,816
It's my mom's birthday, Ohn.

624
00:37:32,841 --> 00:37:36,056
I'm not joking.
It's her birthday, after all.

625
00:37:36,080 --> 00:37:39,336
I just want your mom to have
what makes her most comfortable.

626
00:37:39,361 --> 00:37:42,200
♪ I'm the Queen, after all ♪

627
00:37:42,432 --> 00:37:43,498
Hey.

628
00:37:45,054 --> 00:37:47,800
But I want you
to go with me, Mr. Ohn.

629
00:37:50,895 --> 00:37:52,320
Then let me think about it first.

630
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:58,695
If you see Mae Champi as
more important than my mother,

631
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:00,360
then it's up to you, Ohn.

632
00:38:02,822 --> 00:38:04,495
And this wanting me to go...

633
00:38:04,520 --> 00:38:06,840
Is it for you?
Or for your mom?

634
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,960
Where are you going?

635
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:13,800
Swimming.

636
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:16,440
Jee...

637
00:38:23,526 --> 00:38:25,000
"Can you not bring Ohn?"

638
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,320
"Afraid Mom will be embarrassed"

639
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:27,840
"And this wanting me to go..."

640
00:38:27,865 --> 00:38:30,425
"Is it for you?
Or for your mom?"

641
00:38:39,468 --> 00:38:41,800
Jee, I'm getting in with you.

642
00:38:58,236 --> 00:39:00,680
Jee, aren't you coming?

643
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:03,200
Jee?

644
00:39:06,530 --> 00:39:07,530
Jee!

645
00:39:47,237 --> 00:39:48,237
Ohn!

646
00:39:54,080 --> 00:39:55,440
Hey Fabs!

647
00:39:59,928 --> 00:40:01,240
Hey Fabs!

648
00:40:02,271 --> 00:40:03,834
Come here.

649
00:40:06,582 --> 00:40:07,600
Yes, Mom.

650
00:40:08,145 --> 00:40:10,040
It's "Spectrum Fabulous."

651
00:40:10,355 --> 00:40:11,480
Yeah, yeah.

652
00:40:11,863 --> 00:40:14,720
Too long. 'Fabs' is easier.

653
00:40:16,137 --> 00:40:17,137
Here...

654
00:40:17,679 --> 00:40:19,215
I brought you some lip balm.

655
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:22,603
It makes your lips soft and moist,
and gives a little tint too.

656
00:40:22,628 --> 00:40:25,079
Wear it when you play volleyball.

657
00:40:25,104 --> 00:40:27,680
Win or lose doesn't matter.
We have to look beautiful first.

658
00:40:28,533 --> 00:40:31,219
I'll be dancing and cheering
for you on the sidelines, okay?

659
00:40:31,244 --> 00:40:32,370
- Yes, Mother.
- Yes, Mother.

660
00:40:33,033 --> 00:40:34,093
Come on.

661
00:40:43,567 --> 00:40:46,095
If I'm short on anything,
Aom covers it anyway.

662
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:48,640
This is Ohn asked me
to give it to you.

663
00:40:48,640 --> 00:40:51,143
He forgot to get some cash.
I just remembered right now.

664
00:40:51,168 --> 00:40:53,520
It's not my money, it's Ohn's.

665
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:02,080
I'll take care of you.

666
00:41:02,680 --> 00:41:05,413
I save money every month...

667
00:41:05,438 --> 00:41:08,768
If we spend it carefully,
it's enough to last a lifetime.

668
00:41:12,762 --> 00:41:16,056
"And The Winner is..."

669
00:41:22,832 --> 00:41:24,000
It's because of Jee .

670
00:42:08,056 --> 00:42:12,958
"You're not bringing Ohn, right?
So mom won't be uncomfortable."

671
00:43:11,912 --> 00:43:13,080
"I can't sleep tonight."

672
00:43:14,857 --> 00:43:16,310
"And for the nights that follow..."

673
00:43:17,268 --> 00:43:18,360
"both him and I"

674
00:43:19,713 --> 00:43:20,720
"have trouble sleeping."

675
00:43:42,947 --> 00:43:48,624
"Saturday"

676
00:44:15,294 --> 00:44:16,312
Hmm?

677
00:44:16,337 --> 00:44:19,672
"A gift for your mom."

678
00:44:32,712 --> 00:44:37,719
"You're not bringing Ohn, right?
So mom won't be uncomfortable."

679
00:44:41,905 --> 00:44:44,585
Received with thanks.

680
00:44:53,978 --> 00:44:55,240
Oops!

681
00:45:13,508 --> 00:45:18,522
"Jee, I'd love go to
your mom's birthday with you."

682
00:46:07,152 --> 00:46:09,948
"Received with thanks."

683
00:46:21,985 --> 00:46:25,880
Well, someone's smiling big time.

684
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:28,246
Jee must have texted
to make up with you, huh?

685
00:46:29,360 --> 00:46:30,480
Make up? Pfft.

686
00:46:30,960 --> 00:46:33,360
It was a very cold text message.

687
00:46:36,835 --> 00:46:37,835
Mom.

688
00:46:40,320 --> 00:46:41,600
If my boyfriend dumps me,

689
00:46:42,218 --> 00:46:43,480
can I come live with you?

690
00:46:46,640 --> 00:46:50,160
If he was going to dump you,
would he send you the text?

691
00:46:52,238 --> 00:46:53,238
Hmm?

692
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:57,706
Being made up is better than
being haunted, you know?

693
00:46:58,836 --> 00:47:00,700
Are you talking about
a man or a ghost?

694
00:47:00,725 --> 00:47:02,112
A ghost, of course. I mean...

695
00:47:02,910 --> 00:47:04,016
A man.

696
00:47:09,450 --> 00:47:10,560
Some men...

697
00:47:12,253 --> 00:47:14,120
can haunt you
scarier than any ghost.

698
00:47:20,520 --> 00:47:22,720
"I remember one day..."

699
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:25,240
"You weren't wearing
your maid uniform."

700
00:47:26,160 --> 00:47:29,520
"But you dressed up so beautifully
to say goodbye to us."

701
00:47:29,545 --> 00:47:33,760
"Yes! You even said a Prince
had come to pick up Cinderella."

702
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:38,613
"That day, it really looked like
a Prince picking up a Princess."

703
00:47:38,638 --> 00:47:42,720
"I even told Kit that one day,
I was going to be just like you."

704
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:48,333
"Don't follow my example."

705
00:47:54,273 --> 00:47:55,480
"I was stupid."

706
00:47:57,440 --> 00:47:59,650
"I fell head over heels
in love with a man."

707
00:48:01,251 --> 00:48:02,916
"I didn't listen to anyone."

708
00:48:05,000 --> 00:48:06,590
"Even though he hit me,"

709
00:48:07,924 --> 00:48:10,396
"took my money to buy booze,
cheated on me,"

710
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:14,350
"I still stayed with him."

711
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:18,196
"All just because..."

712
00:48:18,221 --> 00:48:20,560
"he said he loved me."

713
00:48:22,866 --> 00:48:23,983
"Once the money ran out,"

714
00:48:25,561 --> 00:48:26,696
"the love faded."

715
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:30,823
"I had nothing left."

716
00:48:34,391 --> 00:48:35,431
"I only have..."

717
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:38,320
- Us.
- Us.

718
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:47,493
But your love was quite classic.

719
00:48:48,779 --> 00:48:50,970
No matter how bad
the lover treats you,

720
00:48:50,994 --> 00:48:54,358
you don't leave
because you think they love you.

721
00:48:54,383 --> 00:48:57,095
Good thing
I don't have a boyfriend.

722
00:48:57,120 --> 00:48:59,796
Otherwise, I'd probably
get fooled just like Mom.

723
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:02,200
Thai!

724
00:49:02,560 --> 00:49:06,815
It's not just gays, kathoeys,
or LGBTQ people who get tricked.

725
00:49:06,840 --> 00:49:08,735
Straight women and men
get tricked too.

726
00:49:08,760 --> 00:49:11,866
People like her ex,
they are walking red flags.

727
00:49:11,891 --> 00:49:14,300
Whoever they date,
they just want benefits.

728
00:49:14,324 --> 00:49:16,870
They just want to take advantage.

729
00:49:16,895 --> 00:49:20,530
I understand that
you like being alone.

730
00:49:20,555 --> 00:49:22,162
You don't want a boyfriend.

731
00:49:22,187 --> 00:49:23,787
But for you to think that

732
00:49:23,811 --> 00:49:26,271
LGBTQ relationships
are just superficial.

733
00:49:26,296 --> 00:49:27,910
I don't think that's okay.

734
00:49:28,414 --> 00:49:32,254
Just look at me and Nidnoi.
How many years we've been together?

735
00:49:33,880 --> 00:49:37,086
Ohn and Jee have been
together for 7 years too.

736
00:49:37,111 --> 00:49:40,927
Mmm. The very itchy Year 7.

737
00:49:41,470 --> 00:49:42,590
Will we survive it?

738
00:49:43,365 --> 00:49:45,090
Oops. Sorry.

739
00:49:46,200 --> 00:49:47,920
I shouldn't have generalized.

740
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,683
Times are good now.

741
00:49:52,292 --> 00:49:54,643
You guys have good love lives.

742
00:49:55,753 --> 00:50:00,110
And even without love,
you can still support yourselves.

743
00:50:00,960 --> 00:50:02,330
Not like in my days.

744
00:50:03,160 --> 00:50:05,770
To be a kathoey,
you had to prove yourself.

745
00:50:06,440 --> 00:50:08,796
You had to be good.
You had to be talented.

746
00:50:09,920 --> 00:50:13,196
Even then, someone still came
and tricked me out of my money.

747
00:50:16,839 --> 00:50:18,986
If it weren't for people
of your generation, Mom,

748
00:50:19,011 --> 00:50:21,976
my generation wouldn't be
where we are today.

749
00:50:28,880 --> 00:50:31,143
Why did you ask us to
bring you to the school, Mom?

750
00:50:31,720 --> 00:50:33,015
Yeah, Mom.

751
00:50:33,040 --> 00:50:36,310
There are plenty of fancy malls.
Why didn't you want to go there?

752
00:50:37,040 --> 00:50:39,681
Or do you think
we don't have money?

753
00:50:39,706 --> 00:50:41,840
Even if these two don't, I do!

754
00:50:43,527 --> 00:50:47,016
Why would I go to a fancy mall?

755
00:50:47,592 --> 00:50:49,023
I wanted to come here.

756
00:50:49,638 --> 00:50:51,000
My workplace.

757
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:54,350
Even though I was just a janitor,

758
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:57,916
this school gave me a salary.

759
00:50:58,760 --> 00:51:00,230
It wasn't much.

760
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:02,640
But I was happy.

761
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:07,950
This is how old people
reminisce about the past.

762
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:12,161
Especially seeing you guys.
The Fabs Gang.

763
00:51:12,186 --> 00:51:13,186
Mother.

764
00:51:13,480 --> 00:51:16,130
- It's Spectrum Fabulous!
- It's Spectrum Fabulous!

765
00:51:17,080 --> 00:51:18,080
Right, right.

766
00:51:19,166 --> 00:51:20,610
Come on, everyone!

767
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:23,883
- Spectrum Fabulous!
- Spectrum Fabulous!

768
00:51:24,112 --> 00:51:26,000
- Woo!
- Woo!

769
00:51:32,255 --> 00:51:36,971
"She probably gets such good energy
from the people she trusts."

770
00:51:36,996 --> 00:51:38,960
"Look at her.
She's so cheerful now."

771
00:51:40,663 --> 00:51:42,560
"With energy like this,
she can go anywhere."

772
00:51:43,760 --> 00:51:46,472
Let's go, I'll take you myself.

773
00:51:46,496 --> 00:51:48,292
- Wait for us.
- Let's go!

774
00:51:54,873 --> 00:51:57,240
"Gets energy
from people she trusts?"

775
00:51:58,160 --> 00:52:00,440
"My house really
isn't a safe space, is it?"

776
00:52:07,306 --> 00:52:13,060
"Happy Birthday, Mama Tum"

777
00:52:31,520 --> 00:52:32,520
Hello?

778
00:52:33,180 --> 00:52:34,674
"Jee."

779
00:52:34,699 --> 00:52:35,880
"How are you doing?"

780
00:52:37,760 --> 00:52:39,160
Well... okay...

781
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:41,800
Are you uncomfortable?

782
00:52:44,459 --> 00:52:45,520
Bearable...

783
00:52:54,785 --> 00:52:55,785
Jee!

784
00:52:56,391 --> 00:52:57,391
Jee!

785
00:52:57,801 --> 00:53:00,760
Come take a family photo. Quickly!

786
00:53:01,886 --> 00:53:03,393
Where are you, Ohn?

787
00:53:05,800 --> 00:53:07,640
I brought Mae Champi
to see the Morlam concert!

788
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:10,773
But it looks like...

789
00:53:10,797 --> 00:53:13,417
she doesn't want to
just watch anymore!

790
00:53:17,525 --> 00:53:20,720
Jee, tell your mom
Happy Birthday for me.

791
00:53:21,920 --> 00:53:23,320
I love you, Jee!

792
00:53:23,345 --> 00:53:24,440
What?

793
00:53:24,464 --> 00:53:25,504
Come on!

794
00:53:25,529 --> 00:53:26,780
I can't hear you.

795
00:53:27,820 --> 00:53:29,560
I LOVE YOU, JEE!

796
00:53:47,488 --> 00:53:48,666
Sorry about that.

797
00:53:48,691 --> 00:53:50,856
My Love's just called.

798
00:53:50,881 --> 00:53:52,282
What Love?

799
00:53:52,868 --> 00:53:54,669
I've introduced you
to so many girls,

800
00:53:54,693 --> 00:53:56,693
and you weren't interested
in any of them.

801
00:53:57,391 --> 00:53:59,895
- My gift for you.
- Mmm. Thanks, son.

802
00:53:59,920 --> 00:54:02,053
- And this is from Ohn.
- Oh, okay.

803
00:54:02,078 --> 00:54:03,120
Happy Birthday.

804
00:54:03,120 --> 00:54:04,393
Yes, my darling son.

805
00:54:04,418 --> 00:54:06,600
Mmm... love you so much.

806
00:54:08,240 --> 00:54:09,240
Okay, photo time!

807
00:54:09,265 --> 00:54:11,371
Let's take the photo now.
Squeeze in closer, please.

808
00:54:11,396 --> 00:54:12,431
Yes.

809
00:54:14,557 --> 00:54:16,800
Look at the camera. 1, 2, 3!

810
00:54:43,977 --> 00:54:45,377
"Isan NaKhonSil"

811
00:54:59,653 --> 00:55:01,080
"Living next to a concert stage..."

812
00:55:01,520 --> 00:55:03,110
"might make sleeping a bit harder."

813
00:55:03,926 --> 00:55:07,320
"But tonight, many people
will probably have sweet dreams."

814
00:55:07,768 --> 00:55:11,462
"Because they got to release
their feelings with the music."

815
00:55:11,487 --> 00:55:15,160
"And dance to celebrate with
the families they built together."

816
00:55:16,095 --> 00:55:17,320
"Goodnight."

817
00:55:18,654 --> 00:55:24,320
♪ A life without men isn't hard
Just be beautiful in your way ♪

818
00:55:42,615 --> 00:55:45,735
"Love Horoscope:
Unleash the fire within you."

819
00:55:45,760 --> 00:55:47,000
"Go for it!"

820
00:55:47,910 --> 00:55:50,207
"But do you have a boyfriend?"

821
00:55:50,895 --> 00:55:53,695
"Are you sure that..."

822
00:55:54,280 --> 00:55:56,295
"you really want to
try something like this?"

823
00:55:56,320 --> 00:55:58,239
"Let's swim."

824
00:55:58,264 --> 00:55:59,310
"Or is it that..."

825
00:55:59,335 --> 00:56:01,408
"we two siblings
just have cold hearts?"

826
00:56:01,433 --> 00:56:03,381
"No interest in what happens
in the bedroom?"

827
00:56:03,413 --> 00:56:05,584
"Will history repeat itself, Aom?"

828
00:56:05,609 --> 00:56:10,080
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

829
00:56:10,080 --> 00:56:13,709
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

830
00:56:13,733 --> 00:56:16,740
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
